COMMANDS

Django
Create new project: django-admin startproject (project name)
Run project: python3 manage.py runserver
Create an app: django-admin startapp (app name)


1. Create a new project
2. Inside project, create an app
3. In projects setting install the app
4. Inside the app folder create a urls file 
5. In the project urls inport include
6. Create a default url/path and include your app's urls file
7. In the apps url files within the urls pattern create a default path/urls and specify function. Don't forget to import views.
8. In the views files, define the function referenced in the app.urls


How to create a super user: python3 manage.py createsuperuser

How to run a migration: python3 manage.py migrate

To ensure that an object has been successfully propagated into project:
    1. Make a migration
    2. Run a migration

C.R.A.D operation
Create, Read, Add, Delete


HOW TO INCLUDE MEDIA FILES IN DJANGO

1. Create media directory in the project
2. import os in the settings.py 
3. Scroll downwards to where there is STATIC_URL then define the variables
                MEDIA_URL = '/media/'
                MEDIA_ROOT = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, 'media')
4. Go to project urls and import 
    -from django.conf.urls.static import static
    -from django.conf import settings
5. After the square bracket add; +static(settings.MEDIA_URL, document_root=settings.MEDIA_ROOT)



HOW TO START A SERVER
1. Download XAMPP
2. Open its location in the terminal 
3. chmod 755 (file name) xampp-linux-x64-8.2.4-0-installer.run
4. sudo ./xampp-linux-x64-8.2.4-0-installer.run
5. To run it: sudo /opt/lampp/lampp start


